Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low urine specific gravity and normal blood glucose. These findings suggest impaired renal function, possibly chronic kidney disease, and abnormal renal handling of glucose and protein. The low HbA1c excludes chronic hyperglycemia. Urine abnormalities (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal) may indicate underlying renal pathology. Further nephrological evaluation is recommended.
